    "body": "if you are at AWS with gp3/gp2 then i/o latency(not throughput) of EBS is what limits you\r\nto get more you can either switch to io1/io2 (which is expensive as hell) or Instance Store NVME\r\n\r\nwe don't have any specific recommendations about AWS, just general knowledge: disk latency is the current bottleneck (more RAM may help a bit) - especially for big chains like BSC. \r\n",
